column23: The Old Man in the Sea

column3: You sense a new legend might be told this day...
column4: You no longer sense anything out of the ordinary.

column3: It smells of a rat...
column4: The stench has abated.

column3: You sense something deep beneath the magma...
column4: You no longer sense anything out of the ordinary.

column3: Something glimmers near the river bed...
column4: You no longer perceive anything out of the ordinary.

column3: You sense the lord of these skies has returned...
column4: You no longer sense anything out of the ordinary.

column3: Lady Luck has sidled up beside you...
column4: The good lady has departed.

column3: Something wondrous this way comes...
column4: You no longer sense anything out of the ordinary.

column3: The lake begins to radiate with the colors of the rainbow!
column4: The glow fades...

column3: The stones beneath the water begin shifting hither and thither.
column4: The stones are stationary once again.

column3: A massive shadow slides across the loch floor.
column4: The shadow is no more.

column3: You see the flickering light of eyes beneath the waters.
column4: The flickering light fades...

column3: You sense eyes staring up at you from the sandy waters...
column4: You no longer sense anything out of the ordinary.

column3: A large shadow dances along the loch floor.
column4: The shadow is no more.

column3: The visage of a gormless-looking Roegadyn stares at you from beneath the waters.
column4: The face vanishes back into the depths.

column3: The ocean begins to twinkle like the stars in the sky.
column4: The twinkle fades to nothing.

column3: A shadow evoking the Lord of the Whorl slithers across the ocean.
column4: The shadow has disappeared.

column3: The coral begins to wriggle about on the ocean floor.
column4: The wriggling stops.

column3: You see a metallic glint just beneath the waters.
column4: The glint vanishes.

column3: A massive boulder begins to writhe on the ocean floor.
column4: The boulder ceases to move.

column3: You spot a glimmer of crimson, as if a ruby has floated to the surface of the ocean.
column4: All hint of crimson vanishes.

column3: The shadow lurking under the surface belongs to a beast spoken of only in legend.
column4: The shadow is no more.

column3: An aura of violent menace rises from the depths!
column4: The sense of menace dissipates.

column3: You glimpse the writhing silhouette of some vast tentacle moving just beneath the water.
column4: The undulating shadow has withdrawn.

column3: You glance down into a pair of astoundingly goblin-like eyes.
column4: You no longer feel the weight of that goblin-like gaze.

column3: You rub your eyes, certain you'd seen a creature with no business being out on the ocean.
column4: The out-of-place creature has moved on...or never was.

column3: A graceful, leafy form appears, swirling and dancing beneath the waves.
column4: The leafy form has swept on out of sight.

column3: A dull cracking and crunching sound echoes up from the sea floor.
column4: The crunching, cracking sounds fade into silence.

column3: A large fin breaches the ocean surface!
column4: The fin sinks under the surface and out of sight...

column3: A lethal predator draws close to the ship!
column4: The predator loses interest...

column3: A strip of red and white floats under the water's surface!
column4: You lose sight of the colorful fish...

column3: Something blue glitters deep under the water!
column4: The glittering vanishes...

column3: You feel hungry eyes track your every move!
column4: The hungry thing decides to feast elsewhere...

column3: The sea temperature rises suddenly!
column4: The temperature of the water returns to normal...

column3: The seaweed glimmers with a strange light!
column4: The seaweed glimmers no more...

column3: The scent of plums rises from the waters!
column4: The scent of plums disappears...

column3: You spot a massive shadow drifting along beneath the clouds.
column4: The shadow is no more.

column3: You glimpse the blurred form of some flying creature as it flashes across the sky.
column4: Like a living bolt of lightning, the creature flickers past and is gone.
